title: Capacity factor of nuclear power plants in the U.S. 1975 to 2018
summary: In general Capacity factor has rose over the Year.
Capacity factor is slightly increasing from 1985 to 1995.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 1990 and 1995.
The highest Capacity factor, of value 77.4 was reached at Year 1995
The lowest Capacity factor, of value 58.0 was reported at Year 1985
